<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="724" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d724">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 867.48/676</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the President of the Armenian National Delegation</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_NB1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Boghos
                                Nubar</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-27">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 27, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department acknowledges the receipt
                            of your letter of September 12, 1917, in which you state that the
                            Armenian National Delegation deems it necessary to be represented in
                            Washington, and has designated as such representative, Mr.
                                <persName>Miran Sevasly</persName>, who has been already elected by
                            his fellow countrymen, president of the Armenian National Union of
                            America.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PW1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>